logo reveal! (hard launching even though it’s been my logo for over a year lol) 🚀💕

here’s what I wrote about it a year ago: “my last brand kit was my final project in my design class during my junior year at Penn State in 2019. It was great for my first round of applying to jobs but after the entire pandemic and a few different experiences, I’ve grown a lot and it didn’t fit me anymore.
I wanted an organic feel and a brand that could constantly be growing with new icons and assets so I can be prepared for wherever my work takes me.”

a year later here are my thoughts: as someone who gravitates towards new looks and design trends, it was hard for me to settle on one specific vibe for my brand, but as I’ve incorporated these colors into my everyday work and planning I’ve appreciated the versatility this branding has offered and it feels like me! adding fun colors to the (sometimes) mundane activities of life has been so important. overall I can’t wait to see how my design skills continue to grow and shift under this brand 💡🫶🏻

#graphicdesign #branding #branddesign #logodesign #adobeexpress #animation #adobeillustrator #brandidentity

and it’s new! website relaunch! ta da! ✨

I’m so excited about this. for so long my website was solely focused on being an extension of my resume where I dumped all my projects rather than an interactive creative work that really represented me. this web-design heavy facelift felt like a daunting task so I’m really proud of how it turned out. it looks so fun and showcases the different skills/services I have to offer MUCH better. 

most importantly I created an outreach form! most of my design & branding projects are booked through word of mouth / random texts from friends so this will help me better organize design requests / onboarding potential clients. cheers to girl bossing! 🙆‍♀️

#webdesign #graphicdesign #branding #powerpoint #adobeexpress

seven 🍂

so somehow I never watched the folklore documentary on disney+ and it’s my favorite taylor swift album? it left me feeling so in awe of her creative mind and I wanted to create using the new features I learned about watching the adobe max conference a few weeks ago! (AI text to vector feature in illustrator, and animation in adobe express). AI is helping me to throw out perfectionism and just find the joy in creating something out of nothing!

”Please picture me
In the trees
I hit my peak at seven feet
In the swing
Over the creek
I was too scared to jump in
But I, I was high in the sky
With Pennsylvania under me
Are there still beautiful things?”

a day in the office (ft. french class!!)🇫🇷🗽

sharing more about what it’s like commuting from hoboken into manhattan because when I was in college, I was researching moving to new york and I felt like it had to be manhattan/brooklyn or it would feel like I’m not really doing it. of course there’s days where I wish I lived in the city but I can confidently say hoboken is my favorite place I’ve lived so far in my life!

Also for the first time in 3 years I’m taking a French class! I majored in French in college and have been slowly losing it ever since leaving from study abroad/graduating so I’m so excited to build my confidence with again before 2024 👀🇫🇷

#nyc #hoboken #designer #commute

just drank a full coffee and recorded this voiceover can you tell? BTS of my opposite cover by @sabrinacarpenter 

like I said in the video, I’m trying to switch around the way I create content to protect myself from burnout! In the past, I would have a burst of creative energy, sit and learn the piano chords of a song, record a million takes and expect to get a good one by the end of the night. those creative bursts can be nice but staying up until 3am just to not like the rushed outcome is not a sustainable way to create all the time! trying to be better with that 🤍
